---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import Breadcrumbs from "../components/seo/Breadcrumbs.astro";

const canonicalPath = "/booking-policy/";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Booking Policy | Happy Faces LA"
  description="Booking, travel, Availability Hold, and event policy details for Happy Faces LA."
  canonicalPath={canonicalPath}
>
  <Breadcrumbs
    items={[
      { label: "Home", href: "/" },
      { label: "Booking Policy", href: canonicalPath },
    ]}
  />
  <section class="mx-auto w-full max-w-4xl px-4 py-10">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-extrabold text-slate-900">Booking Policy</h1>
    <div class="mt-6 space-y-8 text-sm leading-relaxed text-slate-700">
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-slate-900">Planning vs. Confirming a Reservation</h2>
        <p class="mt-2">
          Plan My Party is the starting point. Submit your party details, including your event date,
          location, estimated guest count, and services requested. Happy Faces LA reviews those details
          and confirms whether an artist is available.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-2">
          Submitting your party plan does not place the date on our calendar and does not make the
          booking final. Your booking becomes final only after Happy Faces LA confirms artist
          availability and sends confirmation.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-slate-900">Availability Holds and Retainers</h2>
        <p class="mt-2">
          No payment is required when you first submit your party details. If your party is eligible for
          an Availability Hold, Happy Faces LA may offer a 20% retainer authorization after reviewing
          your details. The retainer is collected only through the approved booking flow and is tied to
          artist availability confirmation.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-2">
          If artist availability cannot be confirmed, the authorization is canceled or a refund is
          initiated if a payment has already been captured. The remaining balance is due before services
          begin on the day of your event.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-slate-900">
          Travel Fees
        </h2>
        <p class="mt-2">
          Serving Los Angeles and nearby areas. Share your event city or ZIP code for availability.
        </p>
        <ul class="mt-3 space-y-2">
          <li><strong>0–20 miles:</strong> No travel fee.</li>
          <li><strong>More than 20 through 40 miles:</strong> $25 flat travel fee.</li>
          <li><strong>More than 40 through 60 miles:</strong> $50 flat travel fee; manual booking approval is required.</li>
          <li><strong>More than 60 miles:</strong> Custom plan and manual approval required.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-2">
          Travel distance is measured as a one-way distance from our service origin. Any travel fee is
          disclosed as a separate labeled line item before an Availability Hold is offered. Our service
          origin is not publicly disclosed.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-slate-900">Overtime</h2>
        <p class="mt-2">
          Additional time may be available if the artist's schedule allows.
          Overtime must be requested and approved before the scheduled end time.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-2">
          If approved, overtime is added to the final balance based on the
          services being provided and the additional time requested.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-slate-900">
          Parking &amp; Setup
        </h2>
        <p class="mt-2">
          Client is responsible for providing safe, nearby parking or covering
          required parking fees.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-2">
          Please plan for a clean setup area with enough space for the artist,
          supplies, and guests. Difficult parking, valet-only locations, gated
          access, stairs, or long walking distances may affect setup time and
          should be shared before booking.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-slate-900">
          Safety and Product Standards
        </h2>
        <p class="mt-2">
          Happy Faces LA uses professional-grade face and body art products selected for use in entertainment settings. We do not represent our products as hypoallergenic or as FDA-approved for all skin types; product selection is based on professional practice and artist judgment. Clients with known skin sensitivities, allergies, or medical conditions should notify us before the event begins.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-2">
          Happy Faces LA may photograph or record services for portfolio and promotional use. If you do not consent to photography or recording, please let us know before your event begins.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-slate-900">
          School, Corporate, and Institutional Events
        </h2>
        <p class="mt-2">
          School events, corporate gatherings, and institutional or community events need custom planning.
          Pricing, availability, and services depend on event scale, location, and specific requirements.
          Use Plan My Party or contact us to discuss the event details.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
